        <para>
            <graphic fileref="images/time_out.png" align="center" valign="middle" width="1000px"/>
        </para>
        <para>If you are logged in but have not made any changes for 30 minutes, you will be logged out. Unsaved changes will be lost.</para>
        <para>When you are logged out from the editor you should be redirected to the search function, but instead a message (displayed above) pops up.</para>
        <para>(When you are logged out, you revert to the status of 'guest'. Logged in,'/db/org/library/apps/mods/temp' is where you record is stored until you press <guibutton>Save and Close</guibutton>. However, a guest cannot store records here.)</para>
        <para>To work around this issue, delete everything that follows "/exist/library/" in the URL and press <guibutton>Enter</guibutton>. This returns you to the search function where you have to log in again in to continue using the editor.</para>
